<br>
Well, I have recently figured out an &quot;easy&quot; way to get xp.  First, procure a KEI buff.  This buff is sometimes free, but will generally run from 50-100p.  Then, make sure you have these spells memorized.  Root, Snare, Winged Death (53rd dot) stacks with previouse dot.  You will do 3 pairs of dots, 2-3 snares, and sometimes only 1 root.  This is good enough to kill an Frost Giant Elite in GD.  You can actually kill 2 at the same time with a little added work, but same formula applies.  It takes an average of 3 mins per kill, and add up to 1-2 mins per add.  You will have to med an average of 3-10 mins depending on how many times it breaks root, or if you forget to sit down.  Not to say I have done that way to many times or anything.  :-)<br>
By the time kei wears off, you will have made 3 blue bubs, and an average of 200 plat of loot and cash.  I pay an average of 50p per kei, so you can see the potential for profit.  <br>
<br>
Now I have been doing this as early as 48.  This is not a recommended procedure.  If you wait til at least 49, It will take you an average of 10-15 mins per kill, but the rewards can still out number the original pay price of kei.  And you can still walk away with 1 to 1/2 blue bubs if done right.<br>
<br>
As for the area, It is essential that you find a spot with very little walk throughs.  A good spot for this is to follow the stream from thurgadin down to the wurm caves and hang a left.  Go into the rivene.  You will see a tent with what looks like steam/firepit on the ground.  if you click on it, Broodmother will highlite in your target box.  Do not attack.  She should be indif, and it isn't worth annoying her.  This are should be more than an ample pulling zone.   You will have great success with little adds if you pull form above the tent on the plateu in that area.  always remember to pull down to flat ground past tent.  The giants can multiply like sugar ants.  This is not pleasant.<br>
<br>
Start hunt by snare pulling.  Very important, they are almost as fast as you are in wolf/sow'd.  If snare fails, outrun them and stop.  Start clicking root as fast as you can.  In theory, it will go off in time to either just be out of range, or get hit once or twice.  Then snare as often til it sticks.  They have a high resistance, and I have had a giant break root as many as 10 times in one combat, and saved a half dozen times.  After you are successfull with these first 2, let the fun begin.  You will find out that nuking doesn't work as well as your dots if your patient.   You will spend more time meditating if you go nuke happy.  <br>
<br>
Primary Buffs to have prepped:  Wolf/Sow, SLN, Str, Chloro and thorns/thorn coat if your paranoid.  Wait til FM before putting thorns on.  Then med to at least 95% before you go hunting, if you don't have kei.  In theory, you shouldn't be hit, but better to be safe than sorry.  After all, A thorned druid is harder to swallow.  <br>
<br>
Extra insentive to take your time.  FG's hit on average of 50-150 pts of dmg give or take in quick strikes.  <br>
Hope this formula helps you to gain levs quick when you just can't seem to find a group.  Always remember: Everyone loves a druid, but everyone isn't always around.  <br>
<br>
Happy hunting,<br>
<br>
